 Mrs Gretli Steyn was travelling with her husband, Piet Steyn (47) and their two children, Marli (18) and Pieter (10) at the time of the accident. According to eye witnesses, the driver of an Isuzu double cab lost control of his vehicle in the rain and then veered into oncoming traffic. Authorities have confirmed that the Isuzu was carrying five occupants, including a four month old baby. Also read: Baby among 5 who perished in horrific N4 crash The driver, who was coming from Malelane, had stopped to pick up two hitch hikers. The driver, one unknown female and one unknown male, both died upon impact.
The four month old baby was rushed to Life Midmed Hospital by bystanders but later passed away. The baby’s mother remains hospitalised. Also read: #TrafficUpdate: N4 eastbound grinds to a halt after accident claims four lives near Middelburg According to reports, the Steyn family have sustained serious injuries, however, they are in a non critical condition. Mrs Gretli Steyn was the owner of GMC Debt Solutions in Lydenburg.    Parents frustrated by a lack of space in Middelburg schools Traffic officers to appear in court for corruption #TrafficAlert: Two dead in Kranspoort accidents VIDEO: Two perish after truck jack-knifes • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za